JEAN FOURASTIE; ECONOMIST WHO AIDED RECONSTRUCTION OF FRANCE 
Jean Fourastie, 83, economist who helped oversee the reconstruction of postwar 
France. 
A longtime commentator for the newspaper Le Figaro and the news magazine 
l'Express, Fourastie worked alongside Jean Monnet and Pierre Masse in planning 
economic and industrial policies after World War II. He had headed the Academy 
of Moral and Political Sciences and was the author of numerous books including 
"The Great Hope of the 20th Century" in 1949, "40,000 Hours" in 1965 and "From 
One France to Another" in 1986. On Wednesday in the Lot region of France. 
